ning `but absorb` without arguments absorbs ALL uncommitted changes across all branches, which may not be what you want.\n\nView and manage GitButler configuration.\n\n```bash\nbut config\n```\n\n### `but gui`\n\nOpen GitButler GUI for current project.\n\n```bash\nbut gui\n```\n\n### `but update`\n\nManage GitButler CLI and app updates.\n\n```bash\nbut update\n```\n\n### `but alias`\n\nManage command aliases.\n\n```bash\nbut alias\n```\n\n## Global Options\n\nAvailable on most commands:\n\n- `--status-after` - After a mutation command, also output workspace status. Supported on: `rub`, `commit`, `stage`, `amend`, `absorb`, `squash`, `move`, `uncommit`.\n- `-C, --current-dir <PATH>` - Run as if started in different directory\n- `-h, --help` - Show help for command\n\n## Getting More Help\n\n```bash\nbut --help                    # List all commands\nbut <subcommand> --help       # Detailed help for specific command\n```\n\nFull documentation: <https://docs.gitbutler.com/cli-overview>\n","tool_name":"exec_command","tool_kind":"exec","tool_input":null,"exit_code":0,"outcome":"succeeded","source_record":{"timestamp":"2026-05-29T16:30:28.209Z","type":"response_item","payload":{"type":"function_call_output","call_id":"[REDACTED:entropy]"}}}